== Sweetcorn Salsa ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Chop the @tomato{1%medium}(chopped into 1cm pieces) and pop into a #large bowl{}.

Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and sweetcorn.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together and set your salsa aside.

== Cajun Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside, ~{7-9%mins}.

Stir in the @Cajun spice mix{1%tbsp} and garlic, then cook for ~{1-2%mins} more. Remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Warm Tortillas ==

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%mins}.

== Sweet Chilli Slaw ==

Meanwhile, combine the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} in a #medium bowl{}.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} to the dressing and stir well to coat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

== Assembly ==

When everything is ready, pop the tortillas (3 per person) on your plates.

Top with a handful of the @wild rocket{20%g} and the Cajun chicken - as much as you'd like.

Finish with some sweet chilli slaw and a spoonful of the sweetcorn salsa.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in! Enjoy!